  "description": [
    "Page Two JEWISH UNITY Natural and Synthetic i By W LAWRENCE LIPTON There are Jewish Chamberlains in America who are more interested in their special class prerogatives than in the conservation of the rights of the Jews as individuals and as a collective This is the assertion of the vigorous author of Brother The Laugh Is Bitter who declares that much of the Jewish organizational leadership in America is supine unrealistic and reactionary He concludes that Jewish unity exists All it needs is strong leadership The Editor Too many of the discussions now going on about the internal conflicts between Jews and the need for unity in Israel have a bout them the nearleather smell of the synthetic One hears a great deal about religious differ ences and differences in moral ideology but almost nothing a bout the really immediate and material differences that spring from the everyday problems of life Yet it is chiefly these ma terial things that lie at the root of the conflicts among Jews And by the same token it is here that we may find our best hope for unity Talk to any Jew you meet and you will find if you approach him"
  ],
